  "text": "[46] Testing this proposition requires knowledge of the amount of water necessary to erode the valley networks, the total amount of water available to hydrothermal systems, and the actual hydrothermal discharge produced. An estimate of the required water volume for valley erosion may be made from values of areal coverage, drainage density, valley cross section, and sediment-towater ratio. Using a map of drainage densities [CITATION_1] , we estimate the total area covered by valley networks to be about 1.4 Â 10 7 km 2 . Since we estimated earlier that only one quarter of the valley networks may preserve direct interaction with hydrothermal systems, we use a reduced effective area of 3.6 Â 10 6 km 2 . [CITATION_2] calculated a globally averaged drainage density of 0.0032 km",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "129593085",
